description: From Latin porrectus, past participle of porrigō (“stretch out”).

adjectives.description: porrect (comparative more porrect, superlative most porrect)

examples: The palpi of moths in the genus Thumatha are porrect and slender.

verbs.description: porrect (third-person singular simple present porrects, present participle porrecting, simple past and past participle porrected)

examples: The Court said, it was a general rule, that the Wife's Proctor, at this stage of the cause, was at liberty to porrect his Bill of Costs, as against the Husband.
